node.text:
Turner update:
She is fully recovered from her surgery three weeks ago to remove a cancerous tumor from her jaw. Back to running in the yard, chilling in the studio, chasing cats, and being her sweet self! We’re hoping that it doesn’t come back and enjoying all the moments we have together. She does seem a bit more affectionate in recent days. And she now has this badass snaggle tooth look. Thank you so much for all the well wishes and positive vibes ❤️ 

#mygirl #twoturners #happytogether #dogsofinsta #oldgirl #snaggletooth

Developing a new tool and putting the prototype through the ringer! 💪 

This is something that I encourage my students to do if they want to practice the cut across the bottom of the bowl- chuck up a piece of wood and go straight to that cut- but add some distance between the tool rest and the wood to make it realistic. 

When a piano player wants to perfect a certain few measures, they practice those few measures until it sounds right. Why play the entire song every time if you’re only trying to improve one part?
